animal.description:
Hi, I am Meatball. I am a young adult male dachshund mix. I am current on my vaccinations and I am neutered and heartworm negative.

I can be a little shy when first meeting, but when I get to know you, I will just follow you anywhere you want to go. I love all people; however, I think if there are kids involved, I would prefer older kids and not toddlers. What makes me happy? Well, you of course, but also snuggles and tummy rubs and running after squirrels in the yard. I also love pleasing people and hearing them tell me "Good Boy!". I get along with other dogs too, so I would not mind having another dog to share my home with. My foster mom says I could try losing a couple pounds, so I would really like a fenced in yard where I can run after squirrels, play with other pups, or just explore.

I know, I know... "You sound perfect and are so cute. Why don't you have a home yet?" Well, I did, but I started having seizures and it wasn't something they felt comfortable with, so I came back to AHF. I have seen doctors and I am currently on Levetiracetam for the seizures. I take one pill every 8 hours. This is something I may need forever. At some point things can change and the doctor may stop or change the meds, but that is what I am taking for now. It really is not that big of a deal. I do not have seizures constantly, and I can play and cuddle and do everything any other dog can do.

If you are interested in meeting, I would love that. I do not feel you will regret it if you give me a chance to live a long and happy live with you. Fill out an application if interested in me. My foster mom can also answer any questions you may have about the seizures.

Hope to see you soon!


Email: dogs@almosthomefoundation.org

Almost Home Foundation's adoption requirements:
(1) Be at least 21 years of age;
(2) Have the consent of all adults living in the household;
(3) Have approval from the residence owner;
(4) Have valid ID with current address;
(5) Be approved by Almost Home Foundation as a suitable adoptive home; and
(6) Live in the Greater Chicago Land area. Illinois only
*** Please note that Almost Home Foundation accepts only cash or checks for adoption fees; we do not accept debit or credit cards. ***

animal.description:
You don’t have to travel to a galaxy far, far away to find adventure. Just adopt me, Jedi! I’m a four-year-old, six-pound male chihuahua, fully vetted and vaccinated, neutered, microchipped, and up-to-date on heartworm medications. If you’re in need of a miniature apprentice, I’m ready to fill the role!

The snuggles are strong with this one! Maybe I’m in touch with some magical snuggling Force. Maybe it’s just my soft, sleek black fur. Either way, you won’t find a sweeter companion when it’s time to get cozy in front of the TV! I give great kisses too! I get along well with other dogs, so I’ll fit right in with any troop.

Unfortunately, I’ve had some experiences with the dark side, so I’m a bit slow to trust. I keep my guard up, but you’ll be able to win me over with patience and love. 

Judge me by my size, do you? I may be tiny, but I’ve got a big heart! I’ve had a rough start in life, but with the right family, I know I can be a real hero! I’m looking for a new hope...can you help me find it?

If you are interested in adopting Jedi, please DO NOT SEND A MESSAGE TO OUR RESCUE GROUP.  We are too busy placing dogs in great homes to answer messages and inquiries through the listing site.  

PLEASE GO TO THE LINK BELOW TO COMPLETE AN ADOPTION APPLICATION.
 
www.chihuahua-rescue.com/adoption-application
 
CRT requires an approved adoption application and a home visit for all adoption applicants.  CRT transports to OH, KY, IL, MI, MN, WI.

Georgie is an adorable 13 year old Maltese. Georgie's human owners both passed away and he was left an orphan. He was extremely matted so we had to shave his hair down but he seems to like a short haircut. He is good with other dogs, mostly housebroken and paper trained, but not completely. He has very few teeth left but he still has a great appetite. Other than a perineal hernia which we had surgically repaired, and some teary eyes he is in good health for his age. He is about 7 lbs. 

To adopt this little man, you must meet the following requirements
- at least one other small friendly dog in the household
- preferably a home or condo with a yard or small patio for potty area 
- preferably an owner that is home a lot to give him lots of attention
- an owner that will keep up with his grooming

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Marilyn Monroe but I respond to the name "Ava." My siblings and I were dropped off at the shelter in a box and left overnight! Can you believe that?!? We were named as the Hollywood litter, because what little girl doesn't need a little glamour in their life? Am I right? I have had some false starts in my "happily ever after" but SOCA and my foster family have taken a lot of extra steps to help me. My nervous energy has turned out to be based on confusion, and a lack of confidence. I spent an entire month in very extensive training, and my foster mom has learned what I need as well. I need an adopter that will take what I have learned and continue to work with me down the path I am on. I responded very well to training and new techniques. I currently live with my foster mom, her 10 year old daughter, and other doggies! I love people once I get to know them, and other dogs. I need slow introductions with new people, and a little help when I get too excited.

I am house broken and will communicate when I need to go outside. I can sit, lay down, and love treats! I enjoy jogging with my foster mom because I am really quite the athlete, and have no trouble keeping up. Everyone that meets me loves me, even my new trainer said I was one of his favorites and we really became great friends. I need the right fit and when I find it, I will be your best friend for life. I am very loyal.

My adoption fee is $200 and will include spay, vaccinations and microchip. You can apply to adopt me at www.soca-fbc.org, Adopt A Dog.

animal.description:
Cloud is about 2 year old Aussie mix which means he is over the puppy misbehavior and house broken. Cloud is an adventurer, he loves to go and explore! Cloud was exploring and wondered on to the property of an older couple who could not keep him and called for rescue. Cloud is looking for someone who will keep him active and healthy. He walks well on a leash but would love a fenced in backyard to run in. He is good with other dogs and ok with cats (will chase but wont hurt them). He loves to chew on bones, chase balls plus cuddle and gives the best hugs. This loving guy needs a home that understand he needs to explore. Cloud is medium energy who would make a great camping / hiking partner. He is always ready for the next adventure. Are you ready for a forever adventure with him?

If you are interested, complete the
Adoption Application
on our website at
www.NeedyPaws.org
and we will contact you.

Adopters must live within an hour's drive of St. Louis, MO.

Cloud's adoption fee is $250.00, which includes up-to-date vaccinations, heartworm testing and preventative, spay/neuter and microchip.

We are a 100% foster-based rescue and all of our dogs live in approved foster homes. We are dedicated to finding the best Forever Homes, and will perform home visits and conduct veterinarian and reference checks for each potential adopter.

animal.description:
Meet Minnie~

My name is Minnie and I am an 8 year old Terrier/Pit mix from South Carolina.  I weigh roughly 56 lbs.

Even though I didn't have the best 8 years so far, I am a very happy, well adjusted girl. I really enjoy people of all sizes and I am great with my fellow canines. I don't bark a lot at all, and I am super chill. 
My legs look a little different, but I was born this way. It doesn't stop me from getting around and enjoying life!
If you want an easy keeper or a great first dog, I am your girl!

With my adorable looks, and unbridled loyalty, I will always be there for you through thick and thin. I will never judge you, or turn my back on you. Every single day, you will look at me and you will know that you are loved unconditionally. I will never betray you or hurt you, and I will grow old by your side.

******IMPORTANT - PLEASE READ ALL THE GREAT INFO BELOW******

***Please don't apply unless you are very serious about adopting, and are ready to move forward with the adoption process. We are super busy and make a great effort to respond back to EVERYONE ASAP! WHEN WE TAKE THE TIME TO PROCESS AN APPLICATION AND RESPOND BACK TO THE APPLICANT JUST TO BE EITHER IGNORED OR BE TOLD THEY CANNOT COME FOR SEVERAL DAYS, MORE TIME IS WASTED~PLEASE HAVE MORE RESPECT THAN THAT!

PLEASE read our website's ADOPTION PROCESS PAGE prior to submitting an adoption application. www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-process 
ADOPTION APPLICATION: www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-application 

ABOUT OUR RESCUE DOGS: 
 All of our dogs are located in Connecticut, are spayed or neutered, up to date on vaccines, microchipped, have been given deworming medications, and have had CT State health checks, & go home with a leash, collar, & packet of medical paperwork. 

BREED IDENTIFICATION:
Please understand that many rescue dogs are mixes of multiple breeds. Petfinder allows us to choose up to two breeds per dog. While the shelters and our rescue do our best in accurately identifying breeds, breed identification is not guaranteed. If there is a certain breed that you do not want, it is very important that you share this with our rescue when applying. When adopting a puppy, breed uncertainty plays a big part in the size/look of the dog as an adult. Please know that any puppy can be a wonderful dog, regardless of preconceived notions of certain breeds, but it is very important that the adopter has the dedication and patience to raise the puppy with boundaries, consistency, structure, & love. The more effort you give towards training & time you allow for exercise, your puppy will grow to be a HUGE source of UNCONDITIONAL LOVE, TOTAL LOYALTY, HAPPINESS, COMFORT & COMPANIONSHIP!

ABOUT OUR RESCUE:
We are a small rescue run by volunteers & focused on finding the right match for both our dogs & for you. If you are interested in adopting through our rescue, you first will need to complete an adoption application & be approved as a potential adopter before meeting any of our pups. No need to be intimidated by our application as it allows us to get to know you & your lifestyle. Of course, the more you can share the better! Please also note, while a fenced yard is fantastic, it is not required by our rescue, however, it may be required for a certain dog occasionally.  Once adoption applicants are approved to become potential adopters, we offer private appointments where you can meet one or several dogs at the discretion of the rescue. We offer a unique & pleasant experience focused on finding the perfect match. It is extremely important to us that everyone is treated with respect & that NO ONE IS LEFT HANGING. WE WILL GET BACK TO YOU WITHIN 2 TO 3 DAYS of application submission. If there is a dog you are eager to meet, please  TEXT US DIRECTLY at 203-241-2351 so that we can check the status of your application and move it forward immediately. We look forward to hearing from you and helping you find your new best friend.

*All adult dogs can be cat tested by request.

HOME/RENTER INSURANCE:
SOME PROVIDERS HAVE VERY STRICT POLICIES REGARDING WHICH TYPE OF DOG BREEDS ARE ALLOWED UNDER THEIR COVERAGE. STATE FARM WAS SUGGESTED TO US AS THEY DO NOT PUNISH, DROP, NOR REFUSE YOU DUE TO DOG BREED SHOULD YOU RUN INTO ISSUES WITH YOUR CURRENT PROVIDER.

**Update**  (1/18/21)  Mickey was moved from his temp foster home to a foster home where he can stay until we approve an adopter.   It appears that Mickey's eyesight is very compromised, not sure if he can see light and shadows or not. 
 (1/16/21)  This little man has quite a story to tell!   He was found after a snowstorm by a policeman who heard him crying in the woods.   Based on evidence of foot prints, the officer thinks that little Mickey was dumped in the woods and left to fend for himself.   He said that Mickey had been out there on his own for at least 3 days, and it appeared by the evidence in the snow that Mickey had never left the spot where he was dumped.   Somehow Mickey lived through this ordeal and did not have frostbite, most likely because his paws were packed with dirt and poop.   Mickey made his way to a rescue friend who asked us to bring him into our rescue.   We are not sure yet of his age, but he will be seeing our vet and receiving vax next week.   Mickey is friendly with the other dogs that he has met.   At first he didn't seem to understand being petted and held, but he has warmed up and is doing well.  WOULD YOU LIKE TO MEET LITTLE MICKEY?    We are looking for a foster home in the Leb/Lanc/Hbg area or an adopter in Central PA.   PLEASE EMAIL US AT AngelsAmongUsRS@live.com FOR AN APPLICATION.

animal.description:
Who is the cutest guy in town? PATCHES! I am an inquisitive little guy, (only 9 lbs), probably a Jack Russell and dachshund mix, who found myself all alone and confused until a good samaritan found me and searched for my owner. When no one claimed me, hard to believe, I joined a great rescue group who got me a clean bill of health with their vet, gave me my vaccinations, the big neuter snip snip and a microchip. I am ready to find my forever home! Per my name, I have the coolest coloring with lots of great black 'patches' on my white coat.

I am a young dude, with a medium level of energy who will do well in a home with my own yard to run in and sniff when I do my business. Outdoor supervision is a must! Another small playmate might be fun, too. I haven't met cats yet so an intro would be required. Little kiddos scare me, so my foster mom says kids over 10 only. Your patience and understanding and lots of tender loving care will help me adjust to my new home. I don't ever want to be alone again! Adoption means you are committed to me forever and I will be committed to you too! My foster family will update my bio as they learn more about me so that I am matched with the perfect forever home! I am a snuggler, love to sleep on foster mom's bed, and also walk well on a leash! Are you my forever home?

If interested in learning more about PATCHES, please complete our online application at www.helpadogsmile.org. As the rescue does home visits and stays in close contact with the adopter during the adoption process, only Phoenix area homes will be considered for PATCHES. His adoption fee of $350 helps with medical expenses of the rescue.

animal.description:
6FT FENCE REQUIRED

9 week old Coonhound/Treeing Walker Coonhound, and he is a big goof he is full of energy and already jumping to get out of the puppy pen.Toast is a big love bug. As with all puppies he will need a family that is going to be patient while he is going through potty training and will need to be on a regular potty schedule. He is a hound dog and his nose is to the ground sniffing everything he can. When he gets focused on something he goes full speed ahead.

Please do some research on the breed as they are hounds and have hound traits, they can be high energy dogs that when full grown will need lots of stimulation and exercise, they do not make good apartment dogs as hounds are very vocal, a 6ft securely fenced in yard is a must as with any hound their nose is to the ground and they will follow what they smell and love to run.

They are said to be good family dogs who will be fine with dog courteous children. They are loyal and loving and want to be with their humans all the time.

Highly recommended is getting him into puppy training as soon as possible.

If interested, please complete the Adoption Application on our website at www.NeedyPaws.org and we will contact you. Adopters must live within an hour's drive of St. Louis, MO.

Our $250 adoption fee includes up-to-date vaccinations, heartworm testing and preventative, spay/neuter and microchip.

We are a 100% foster-based rescue and all of our dogs live in approved foster homes. We are dedicated to finding the best Forever Homes, and will perform home visits and conduct veterinarian and reference checks for each potential adopter.

animal.description:
Adoption fee on this dog is $300.

Sammie Jo is a beautiful red and tan female that is approximately 6 years old.  She originally came to us with her litter of puppies in 2018 from a local shelter.  She was adopted out and returned to us in 2019, through no fault of her own.  She unfortunately came back to us overweight at 107 lbs on a 70 lb. frame. 
 
She suffered a torn cruciate in her right rear knee, due in part to her being overweight.  She has slimmed down to her ideal weight around 70 lbs. She had surgery at UC Davis in August of 2020 to repair her knee.  She is fully recovered from her surgery and now ready to go into a home again where she can enjoy life and have a family of her own. 
  
Sammie Jo is super sweet and loves attention.  She does have some ball drive.  She will bring you her ball or toy and wait patiently for you to throw it.  She also has a medium prey drive, so a home with small dogs or cats would not work for this girl. 
  
Sammie Jo knows basic commands and has great recall.  She is a good alarm barker, keeping an eye on things in the home.  She currently lives in a home with 3 adult male GSDs and 1 adult female GSD.  She gets along well with everyone.  She also behaves like a typical mature female, and becomes the fun police if things get too rowdy for her taste.  
 
Sammie Jo needs to work on her leash manners.  She is very strong and has a tremendous amount of pull.   The ideal adopter will need a good center of gravity, in order not to be pulled down. 
 
Sammie Jo needs a home where her food intake will be monitored, and food securely stored.  She needs a home where the owner will appreciate her crafty nature and her problem-solving skills.   She will benefit from being in a home that will provide her with daily exercised and continued training.   

This dog is a Level 2. Please be sure you understand what a dog of this Level requires. Go to our home page for an explanation of the Dog Rating Levels.

For more information and to see when this dog will be attending an Adoption Day, please see our Dogs page on our main website at www.gcgsr.org. 

We operate within a reasonable driving distance from the Greater Sacramento area, the 	Central Valley down to Merced, and Lake Tahoe. A reasonable driving distance is determined by where one of our volunteers is willing to drive within our areas of service. That means we don't adopt out of our area, to Southern California, or Out of State. 


Thank you for visiting!
animal.name: Sammie Jo

Note: Dogs are pack animals and do not do well away from other members of their pack. The adopter is the alpha member of the pack, and the dog or puppy needs as much one-on-one contact with the alpha as possible. For this reason, all Route 66 Rescue Inc. dogs are adopted to inside homes only. They must be on leash, or inside a secure fence when outside, and not left outside alone when no one is home. Invisible fencing does not qualify as protection since other animals and strangers have access to the dog. The dogs must be returned to Route 66 Rescue, Inc. if ever given up by the adopter. Thank you for understanding we want only the best for the dogs you give a forever home.
 
Please complete and return the adoption application to meet any of our adoptable dogs.

animal.description: Meet Beautiful brindle Benni!  This gorgeous and affectionate 6-year-old is so upbeat, friendly and affectionate.  Benni just loves people! She will crawl into your lap and just be so happy if you let her.  Benni weighs 70lbs- is active and very eager to please.  With the help of our volunteers, Benni is working on her basic commands and she walks well on leash. We haven’t tested her with the other dogs at the rescue yet, but are hoping to soon. Benni is very fun girl, very smart and would be a great hiking buddy.  She loves the outdoors and can’t wait to accompany her active family on all their adventures. Benni was rescued by Greyhound Pets from South Korea and we aren’t sure how much "greyhound" there is in her!  Regardless, you won’t find a more deserving and social dog who makes up for her unknown past by being super loving and totally delightful. Benni needs a fenced yard and is not suitable for an apartment/condo/townhome.  She will need a home without cats. She is crate-trained and house-trained and calm in the house and car.  Benni is spayed, vaccinated and micro-chipped and available to meet at Greyhound Pets in Woodinville.  Her adoption fee is $500.  For questions or a link to the adoption adoption application, email Kathy at kkreyling11@gmail.com.  You really have to meet this stunning and loving Shepherd mix who is a gorgeous on the inside as well as out!

Gabby is a 7-9 month old female Boxer mix that currently about 23lbs. Gabby is great with other dogs, kennel trained, and dealing well with house breaking. She will be joining us in Maine on January 30th. 


Adoption fees cover age specific vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm/lyme/ehrlichia test, worming and transport fees. 

Adoption fees: 
Through 6 months of age $450; 
7 months to through 5 years $400; 
6 years and under 9 years $325: bonded pairs are $500; 
9 years and older $250: bonded pairs are $300 

FOR PUPPIES: PLEASE READ!!
Homes considering Puppies must be prepared for:
Flexible Schedules for Potty Training. Puppies can only hold urine for one hour per month of age. Crate Training for the next 10 months to keep them safe from chewing on everything in your home. Supervision with Children and Obedience training. 
Socialization; both with new people, children and other dogs outside of the home.
Homes that want a well behaved dog, must be prepared to put the time, effort and costs associated to train a puppy. Well behaved dogs are not born, they are trained!  Please do not apply for a puppy if you cannot or do not have the time for a puppy.

Almost Home Rescue of New England is a 501 c 3 non-profit rescue; rescuing dogs since 2005. All Adoption applications are completed on line at www.almosthomerescue.net 

This dog is available unless it is marked as Pending, meaning Pending Adoption. This dog is in foster care locally, ONLY if Maine or New Hampshire is listed next to the dogs name; otherwise, the dog is still waiting with our partner rescue for an adoption or foster home in New England. 

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior dogs have a history of being kept up to date on rabies and distemper, have had annual heartworm tests, and are on heartworm preventative at least 6 months of the year. Current pets must by spayed/neutered. 

Imported dogs are transported on a USDA approved transport with a Health Certificate. All imported dogs are quarantined 14 days prior to getting on transport.

This gorgeous 9 month old 52 lb fluffy boy is a St. Bernard mix. Pork Chop is an absolute sweetheart who craves love and kindness. He is a gentle boy that someone has treated harshly -- he sometimes crouches and braces when approached as if expecting to be hit or kicked. As one might expect of a dog named Pork Chop, he's very food motivated and if you offer some tasty treats he is more than happy to be your friend. Once you gain his trust, he will give you a smile and show you his adorable underbite. Pork Chop will likely be around 60 lbs when fully grown, smaller than a St.Bernard, so there's a smaller breed or two in there as well. Pork Chop needs a furever home with a fenced yard and another friendly, playful dog to help build his confidence.

If you'd like meet Pork Chip, please fill out a foster-to-adopt application at
dreamhouserescue.org.
Greater Cincinnati area adopters only please. Pork Chop will need to come back to see us a few times to complete all of the vetting covered by our adoption fee. Pork Chop will go to a furever home on a foster-to-adopt basis, his adoption will be finalized when his vetting is completed. We only adopt dogs into homes where all current pets are spayed/neutered and current on vaccines and heartworm and flea and tick prevention. We do check veterinary references to make sure adopters are compliant with standard veterinary care.

animal.description:
Because we are all volunteers, Illinois Doberman Rescue Plus only considers approved applicants to meet our orphans in our foster homes. Please read our eligibility requirements and apply on our website: www.ildoberescue.com/adopt.  After an application is submitted, additional inquiries can email dobes@ildoberescue.com.

Micah is a handsome gentleman who was transferred from a suburban animal control after a legal hold. He seems well-adjusted and has good manners in his foster home, including appearing to be housebroken! He knows a few commands, but he is very treat motivated, so he can learn some new tricks in a recommended obedience course. Micah will go in his crate, but he prefers to be out where the action is. He seems to be fine around the resident Dobermans in his foster home, but we always recommend a slow intro. He has no known history with cats or kids, but he should be okay with kids 10 and up who know how to act nicely around big dogs. Our vet estimates Micah to be around 7 years old. His heart sounds good, but he has some typical muscle weakness in his hind legs. This may be due to not getting enough exercise, or it could be something else, so he will go back to the vet for more diagnostics next week. He navigates the carpeted stairs well but no slick steps. His foster mom put rugs on the wood floors to help him. He walks nicely on a leash, so hopefully some at-home PT around the block or up/down the stairs will bulk that area up. Micah would appreciate a fenced yard (no e-fence) to play with his toys.

The biographical information provided is correct to the best of our knowledge while the animal is in our care or includes what may have been provided by a previous owner. We strive to be honest and accurate, but animals can change their personalities and behavior when they settle into a new home. IDR+ makes no guarantees based on the information we observe and provide.

animal.description:
Aspen is a 2.5 year old male mixed breed (our vet's best guess: Springer Spaniel mix, though we don't know where he gets his corkscrew tail!). He is fostered with other large dogs and gets along well, He also previously lived with cats and has gotten along with the one he's met while in our care. 
Aspen is a nervous boy who is apprehensive (and very loud) about meeting new people. He seems to warm up more quickly to women, though he is getting used to his foster dad. Because of his uncertainty with new people, we are looking for a home without children. 
He has a lot of puppy energy and will keep you laughing with his playful personality. He loves his toys and loves playing with his furry foster sisters. He will need a family who walks long distances, hikes or runs. Known to be an escape artist, Aspen needs to be leashed and will need a yard with a 6 ft (or higher) fence. 
He is a big snuggler once he gets to know you and has not been left alone for long periods. He gets quite stressed when alone and when in his crate, so would like a family member to be home often with him. If you work from home and do a lot of Zoom, he especially likes to say hi to all the meeting participants! 
We are working on basic commands and leash skills, and Aspen's house training is coming along nicely. He is a smart boy who is eager to please and very loyal to people he knows and trusts.  
Aspen's adoption fee is $250 and includes his neuter, microchip, current vaccinations and deworming,  a leash, collar and some food. Adoption forms and information about the process can be found at www.cleoskarmacaninerescue.com  . We ask that forms are submitted prior to meeting the dogs.  Due to the large number of inquiries that our volunteers receive, we are only able to reply to email messages with an adoption form attached.  
Aspen is currently fostered in Brooks.

animal.description:
Cinderella is a 7-9 month old mixed breed puppy who currently weighs about 37lbs. She is brindle with a black mask. She is a very sweet puppy that is on the submissive side. Cinderella loves to roll over and have her belly rubbed.  

Cinderella will need someone who is going to take the time to work with her in various situations to help her come out her shell. 

She will be joining us in Maine on January 30th.

Adoption fees cover age specific vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm/lyme/ehrlichia test, worming and transport fees. 

Adoption fees: 
Through 6 months of age $450; 
7 months to through 5 years $400; 
6 years and under 9 years $325: bonded pairs are $500; 
9 years and older $250: bonded pairs are $300 

FOR PUPPIES: PLEASE READ!!
Homes considering Puppies must be prepared for:
Flexible Schedules for Potty Training. Puppies can only hold urine for one hour per month of age. Crate Training for the next 10 months to keep them safe from chewing on everything in your home. Supervision with Children and Obedience training. 
Socialization; both with new people, children and other dogs outside of the home.
Homes that want a well behaved dog, must be prepared to put the time, effort and costs associated to train a puppy. Well behaved dogs are not born, they are trained!  Please do not apply for a puppy if you cannot or do not have the time for a puppy.

Almost Home Rescue of New England is a 501 c 3 non-profit rescue; rescuing dogs since 2005. All Adoption applications are completed on line at www.almosthomerescue.net 

This dog is available unless it is marked as Pending, meaning Pending Adoption. This dog is in foster care locally, ONLY if Maine or New Hampshire is listed next to the dogs name; otherwise, the dog is still waiting with our partner rescue for an adoption or foster home in New England. 

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior dogs have a history of being kept up to date on rabies and distemper, have had annual heartworm tests, and are on heartworm preventative at least 6 months of the year. Current pets must by spayed/neutered. 

Imported dogs are transported on a USDA approved transport with a Health Certificate. All imported dogs are quarantined 14 days prior to getting on transport.

animal.description:
Pumpkin is an 8 year old, 17lb American Cocker Spaniel. She is a very sweet girl who needs a quiet home to spend her golden years in. Pumpkin doesn't like to be left home alone and would prefer a family who has somebody home most of the time. She would do best in a home without young children, but would be okay with older kids ages 10+ who can respect her space. Pumpkin is great with other dogs and does not care about cats. She can be a bit shy at first, but once you give her a chance she opens up into a sweet, loving cuddle bug!

This pup's adoption fee is $100, payable in cash only. This includes current vaccines & deworming, spay/neuter (completed before leaving our care), and discounted microchipping upon request at the time of adoption. It also includes an adoption goodie bag and some food to start you off with. 

To adopt, email us about your interest in adopting. We will email our application back to you to download, fill out, and email/fax back to start the process. Once your application has been processed & approved, we will contact you to set up a meet and greet with the pet(s) you are interested in. If all goes well with the meet & greet, the adoption can be finalized and you can take your new furry family member home with you!

animal.description:
Cami is a  4 month old puppy that came from our rescue partner shelter in Louisiana.  She arrived to us along with her brother Cooper.   She would be fine with children 8 and over. 

She is crate trained and is currently working on her house training.  She is very high energy and does not stop, even after long walks. I think she would benefit from a home with lots of people and lots of attention. She is very independent and head strong. She has the typical Mali jump around energy. She has good ball and food drive. She will need an experienced Malinois adopter that will be able to teach her manners. She loves lots of toys. 

Cami is Malinois and will only be placed in a home with prior Malinois experience.  Her new family must be willing to put in the time and training that it will require for Cami to become a good citizen.  

Adoption fees cover age specific vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm/lyme/ehrlichia test, worming and transport fees. 

Adoption fees: 
Through 6 months of age $450; 
7 months to through 5 years $400; 
6 years and under 9 years $325: bonded pairs are $500; 
9 years and older $250: bonded pairs are $300 

FOR PUPPIES: PLEASE READ!!
Homes considering Puppies must be prepared for:
Flexible Schedules for Potty Training. Puppies can only hold urine for one hour per month of age. Crate Training for the next 10 months to keep them safe from chewing on everything in your home. Supervision with Children and Obedience training. 
Socialization; both with new people, children and other dogs outside of the home.
Homes that want a well behaved dog, must be prepared to put the time, effort and costs associated to train a puppy. Well behaved dogs are not born, they are trained!  Please do not apply for a puppy if you cannot or do not have the time for a puppy.

Almost Home Rescue of New England is a 501 c 3 non-profit rescue; rescuing dogs since 2005. All Adoption applications are completed on line at www.almosthomerescue.net 

This dog is available unless it is marked as Pending, meaning Pending Adoption. This dog is in foster care locally, ONLY if Maine or New Hampshire is listed next to the dogs name; otherwise, the dog is still waiting with our partner rescue for an adoption or foster home in New England. 

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior dogs have a history of being kept up to date on rabies and distemper, have had annual heartworm tests, and are on heartworm preventative at least 6 months of the year. Current pets must by spayed/neutered. 

Imported dogs are transported on a USDA approved transport with a Health Certificate. All imported dogs are quarantined 14 days prior to getting on transport.

animal.description:
PLEASE COMPLETELY READ THE ENTIRE DESCRIPTION 

We are a foster home based rescue organization. **Only approved adopters can meet our dogs** 

If you are interested in adopting please follow these instructions before contacting Rescue4All. Virtually all of your questions will be answered by following these instructions: 

1. Go to our website www.rescue4all.org 
2. Thoroughly read through the HOW TO ADOPT tab
3. Thoroughly read through the OUR PROCESS tab
4. then fill out an online application from your laptop or desktop computer or click on the mobile friendly link on the application page.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Willow is a 1yr old pitbull type dog. She came to R4A as a medical transfer needing rescue from the Spokane Humane Society. 

 She was owner surrendered in horrific condition....suffering from severe untreated allergies, a massive skin infection, ear infections, covered in yeast, inflamed, hair loss over her entire body, itchy, hot to the touch, swollen, inflamed, and miserable.

The awesome vet staff at the Spokane Humane Society put her on steroids, treated her for mange (as a precaution), put her on oral antibiotics, medicated baths, and treated her ear infections. 

The vet staff at Spokane Humane Society put “soft claws” over her nails and you can get them for your dog or cat. In Willow’s case this it to try to minimize her causing damage to her skin with her nails. 

We got her allergy tested for both environmental and food allergies so we could see exactly what she needed. 

She has some food allergies: brewers yeast, pork, duck, eggs, beef and cows milk. 

Her biggest problem is environmental allergies which we need to manage.
This includes several grasses, trees, and fungi.

She had happy tail (which we are still battling), her ears were ripped and bloody from her shaking her head because of her ear infections and her entire body is very itchy.

The first goal is to get her body out of this massive allergy attack. 

She does have some anxiety but her foster is working with her to help her learn how to be able to self soothe. 

Despite everything you can can see how much better she looks today and she is happy, social, and just a young silly dog!

MORE ABOUT WILLOW:
https://www.facebook.com/rescue4all/posts/3557724850975870

MONTHLY HEARTWORM DATE:  12th of each month
FOSTER HOME:  Deanna, Decollinss@aol.com
RESCUE #:  2020-12-29-01

BIO UPDATE (1/25/2021): 
If you are home a lot and looking for a companion, Frieda would love to have a home to call her own again.  Once she trusts you, it may take a few days or even a few weeks, she will be your forever companion.  She does very well with other dogs, but prefers the life of a quiet home.  She loves her doggy beds and will sleep there next to your bed all night.  During the day, she will mosey around, take naps, and join you on the couch to lounge some more.  Frieda is not a very active dog, but she does love her meal time!  She is currently on a diet and on a mission to lose another 6 pounds or so.  This girl is so sweet and we are waiting for the perfect home to apply to adopt!  Her wish list includes:
•	A fenced yard
•	Someone home most of the time
•	Someone who has patience because she is terrified
•	Another small dog to keep her company if you have to be gone for any length of time
•	No apartment or high rises

BIO:  Frieda came from middle Tennessee when her owner went into assisted living and had to give her up. 

Frieda was purchased from a breeder at 4 years old and was never socialized before or after purchase. For that reason, she is very timid around new people and has taken sometime to warm up to us.  We see small baby steps each day but whoever adopts her MUST be patient and not push her.  We can tell she wants to be involved with her people, but is just too scared right now. Frieda is doing well on a doggie door but expect accidents until she trusts you enough to have you let her outside. The previous owner said she was not puppy pad trained.

If you are looking to rescue, then here you go... Frieda needs lots of love and patience for her to know she’s safe and that she is with her family for the rest of her life.  

============== Information for All Dogs/Adopters ==============

If you have questions about this dog, please feel free to contact the foster home at the email address listed above.  They have the most up-to-date information concerning the dog and would be happy to answer any questions about the animal. 

We welcome out of state and Canadian adoptions, but we will not ship any dog via cargo.  You will have to make arrangements to pick up the dog or for them to go by ground transport.  If you choose transporting by either volunteers through our organization or by paid transporter, there will be an additional $45 fee added for the required Health Certificate. 

We will not adopt into CT, RI, NH, ME, or MA due to strict laws regarding importation of dogs into those states.  If you have an issue with this, you need to take this up with your legislatures.

To understand the adoption process through AADR, please review the Adoption Information on our home page.  Transportation options are outlined on that page in Step 3.

If you are interested in adopting this Dachshund please review Read Before You Adopt and then you can complete an Application.

THANK YOU FOR YOUR INTEREST IN A RESCUE.

Please don't let the distance stand in your way of finding your newest best friend. We have volunteers that will help your "new friend" get up and down the East Coast. We just can't get them from one Coast to the other but some day we hope to have enough volunteers to do that as well.  For now, please look for dogs on your coast.

animal.description:
Video link: https://youtu.be/x1V-KB-wJnk

FOR ADOPTION! Note: Only those with a responsible dog ownership history and excellent vet reference need apply.

(For more pics, visit nr2r.petfinder.com or www.RoadtoRescueLA.org)

INSTRUCTIONS TO APPLY:

PLEASE read profile thoroughly BEFORE applying:

DOG APPLICATION LINK: http://www.roadtorescuela.org/dog-application

Banderos (male)

Intake date: 10/28/2020

Chihuahua

7 years old

5.12 pounds

Adoption fee: $170, which includes vetting, microchip and microchip enrollment fee

Good with other dogs: yes

Cats: yes

Vetting: altered (spayed/neutered), UTD on shots, heartworm negative, fecal negative, dental performed, on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention, microchipped

Health issues: none found

Temperament: very sweet, wants to be near you, gives kisses (he DID NOT come in that way, though which is why it's taken us so long to post his profile)

Energy level: low; he's fairly chill

Groom needs: low; a bath from time-to-time

Biography: Banderos came to us when his owner became to ill to care for him. The son reached out to us for help and we took him in. He came to us EXTREMELY SCARED, bitey, growly wouldn't eat wouldn't let anyone near him laid in a doggie bed all day and would lunge or bolt if anyone approached. Well, we aren't ones to give up so every day we worked with him. He would jump on the gate when he wanted to come in so we always took that opportunity to pick him up and while he struggled to get away, we held tight. He would slowly calm down and relax. We introduced boiled chicken to him (which he LOVES!). Then all of a sudden like from one day to the next he realized "hey, these people are nice!". It was literally like a switch went off. He now jumps on our legs to be picked up he gives kisses he prances around with confidence etc. He's a changed dog. A huge thanks goes out to all our volunteers who really worked with him and didn't give up (and at the risk of being bit which he never actually did but would warn us by snapping the air). One thing we've noticed now that he wants our attention and to be held is he has become lap possessive of other dogs approaching. This is NOT uncommon so please don't hold it against him. Some little dogs can just be that way. Otherwise, he does fine with the other dogs we've had no problem out of him in that regard. We'd love a home for him that is calm and nurturing patient and kind. If you think you are the person for Banderos, we welcome your application.

**IMPORTANT NOTES**

*We do adopt out of state provided the adopter is willing and able to travel to us once approved. We do not ship or transport our animals and there is no exception to this rule.

*All of our adoptable dogs are small, and they are never to be left outside alone, ever! We only rehome our dogs to adopters that plan to have them as inside dogs and part of the family! We do allow adopters with doggie doors, provided there is SECURE fencing. There is no exception to this rule!

*NO SMALL CHILDREN!! As with almost all the dogs at NR2R, young children or a very active household is not recommended. Many of our dogs come to us BECAUSE of small children, thus we do not rehome our dogs to homes with babies or young children. KEEP THIS IN MIND IF YOU HAVE VISITING GRANDCHILDREN AS WELL! Even if the children are older, it would depend on the child AND the parent or parents.

*HOUSETRAINING: We do NOT guarantee that any of our adoptable dogs are housetrained. While most should be easily trained, keep in mind that they live in a rescue where they have access to the outdoors all day and are inside at night. Even if they were surrendered to us as housetrained, it doesn't mean they will automatically be housetrained in your home. Housetraining them should be easy in the right home with time, patience, and consistency.

*We do not guarantee the age, health or temperament of any of the dogs we rehome. Many of the dogs we take in come from animal control and rarely do we have histories and even when we do, many times the histories are inaccurate.

*Only adopters with a responsible dog ownership history and excellent vet reference need apply. If you bring this pet into your heart and home, you will receive in return many years of love, companionship, and loyalty. That's our guarantee.

Other notes: This pet is available for adoption through Ninna's Road to Rescue, Benton, La. We are 501c3 non-profit organization. Our mission is to rescue small-breed dogs and a handful of cats and to re-home them into RESPONSIBLE and CARING forever homes. DOG APPLICATION LINK: http://www.roadtorescuela.org/dog-application

Time may be of the essence if you are looking to adopt a specific animal. We do not reserve animals, unless and until we have approved your application, provided the animal is still available at the time we receive your application. The first APPROVED application we receive will be considered. We are NOT a first come, first serve rescue!! We adopt our rescues out to the RIGHT home, not just A home. Only responsible pet owners need apply.

Applying to adopt does NOT commit you to the adoption NOR does it guarantee the adoption.

CONTACT: Our adoptable pets are updated regularly, but if you want to check the availability of a pet... OR still have questions AFTER reading this profile, message us via our Facebook page. Please indicate the name when communicating with us.

www.RoadtoRescueLA.org

PLEASE VISIT RESCUE DOG VILLAGE GUARDIAN, INC A 5013C NON-PROFIT ORGAINZATIONS WEBSITE AT WWW.RESCUEDOGVILLAGE.COM PETFINDER HAS MADE CHANGES TO FORMAT OF THE BIO, THEREORE; WE CAN NO LONGER PROVIDE LIVE LINKS TO THE APPLICATION OR AN EMAIL. WE ARE SO SORRY FOR THIS INCONVIENCE. APPLICATION: IF YOU WISH TO TYPE THE PATH TO OUR APPLICATION; YOU WILL NEED TO TYPE IN THE ADDRESS IN THE ADDRESS BAR. HERE IS THE ADDRESS: https://www.rescuedogvillage.com/adoption-application/ EMAIL: IF YOU WISH TO EMIAL RDV YOU WILL NEED TO OPEN YOUR EMAIL ACCOUNT AND TYPE IN THE ADDRESS For more information about this dog, email: ausman@gulftel.com PLEASE VISIT OUR WEBSITE RDV HAS LOTS OF PHOTOS LIVE LINKS TO THE APPLICATION AND AN EMAIL LINK FOR YOUR QUESTIONS. PLEASE NOTE EMAIL: you will need to open your email account and type in the address because live links have been removed by Petfinder APPLICATION: If this dog has stolen your heart, don't wait! Fill out an application https://www.rescuedogvillage.com/adoption-application/ to be considered as a potential forever home through our rescue. PLEASE NOTE APPLICATION: you will need to type the address in the address bar because live NAME: Ramsey GENDER: Male DOB: 08-01-20 WEIGHT: 62.8 lbs As Adult over 100 lbs BREED Great Pyrenees & Karakachan Mix LOCATION: Terryville, CT DONATION: $450.00 Meet Ramsey, a beautiful 4 month old Great Pyrenees/Karakachan mix who just joined our wonderful southern foster along with his brother Ramsey. These brothers had quite a rough start, but foster mom says they are very quickly adapting to “the good life” and will be ready for their forever homes very soon! Their story is sadly a pretty common one. Irresponsible dog owners who do not take care of, nor care about their dogs enough to get them spayed. This owner’s female was purchased to watch his herd of goats and became pregnant. She had a litter of 8 puppies, and instead of finding them homes he decided to keep them locked in a cow trailer! They received no socialization with humans, no daylight, and no fresh air to run around and play in. This heartless man threw food into the dirty trailer for these pups, but as the weeks passed it became apparent that, due to their breed, they were going to be large dogs, and he knew he could not afford to feed them. Again, instead of trying to find them homes, he fed them less and less, until a kind neighbor began feeding them until he could get them help. It was only after the cruel owner confided in the neighbor that he planned to get someone to come over and “get rid of them” that the neighbor jumped into action. He found a rescue group willing to seize the puppies if the owner promised to spay the mother dog and this wonderful neighbor even offered to pay for it! It’s with the help of all the wonderful people out there that these precious pups are able to go on to live happy lives. Several rescue groups stepped up to each take two puppies, and we are delighted to have Brady and Ramsey! Every day they are learning more and more to just be happy puppies. These boys are gorgeous. They have luxurious golden white fur and sweet faces. They now enjoy very much running and playing in the sunshine, and getting lots of human interaction and affection. When choosing a breed that is right for your family, typical characteristics of that breed need to be considered. The Karakachen is an independent working dog, immensely loyal, and devoted to their masters, trying their best to protect their household at any cost. They have a strong smelling and hearing instinct that is instrumental in making them ideal guard dogs. Though not aggressive while guarding their livestock, these territorial dogs display a highly reserved nature while confronting strangers. Apart from their compatibility with children of the family with whom they are brought up, they will also be able to mingle with other smaller pets if socialized well socialized. Frequently described as “majestic,” Great Pyrenees are big, immensely strong mountain dogs standing as high as 32 inches at the shoulder and often tipping the scales at more than 100 pounds. These steadfast guardians usually exhibit a Zen-like calm, but they can quickly spring into action and move with grace and speed to meet a threat. The lush weatherproof coat is all white, or white with markings of beautiful shades of gray, tan, reddish-brown, or badger. They are smart, patient, and calm. The Great Pyrenees is an immensely powerful working dog bred to deter sheep-stealing wolves and other predators on snowy mountaintops. Pyrs today are mellow companions and vigilant guardians of home and family. Ramsey is confident, handsome, graceful, strong, gentle, intelligent, dedicated, loyal and protective. He is a very happy dog that loves all things human and canine, he fits the definition of the breed perfectly, loyal, friendly, smart, courageous, protective but always under control. During our time with this exceptional dog we have been amazed at his gentleness, his intuition and his absolute commitment to his people and their needs. We have found Ramsey above all else to be easy to love, a sweetness that is unrivaled and a beauty that is obvious both externally and internally. Ramsey needs an experienced family, access to a large yard, long walks or runs and an active family that have owned or experience with dogs over 100 lbs. As an adult, his breed requires a confident, experienced owner, one who will gain his respect and understands his independent nature. Ramsey and Brady loves attention, they are active and playful and will make a wonderful companion. He would do well in a house with a large yard and children they can run and play with. Brady and Ramsey have come so far and deserve a loving home where they are safe, have a warm bed, and are considered part of the family. Will you open your heart and home to Brady and Ramsey? The Great Pyrenees is a naturally nocturnal breed. Since many predatory animals are nocturnal, this adaptation better enables the breed to guard farms and homes against potential threats in the night. He needs enough exercise to keep him lean and healthy, but not so much that their soft growing bones, joints, and ligaments become over-stressed and damaged. The need to stay in shape, but not in hot or humid weather for fear of overheating. ABOUT OUR RESCUE RESCUE DOG VILLAGE GUARDIAN, INC A 5513C NON-PROFIT ORGAINZATION WEBSITE: WWW.RESCUEDOGVILLAGE.COM ABOUT OUR RESCUE We go the extra mile for every dog and do whatever it takes to make sure that that dog finds happiness, we give 100% and more. It is what we enjoy doing and helps us wake up in the morning; we know that the dog is thankful we rescued them and thankful for their life. Finally, they will be forever remembered by our families that adopted them because they really rescued them. These dogs deserve all of our attention, and in Rescue Dog Village Guardian, Inc A 5513c Non-Profit Organization, we are committed to our adopters and our dogs equally. We offer full disclosure and hope to make the best matches possible. Please know our adoption fees never cover our expenses. We rely on the generosity of our adopters and supporters to help us help the dogs. MASSACHUSETTS RESIDENTS This dog cannot be adopted to Massachusetts residents due to new laws regarding rescue dogs being prohibited from adoption. Please contact Patricia Cabral or Mike Cahill for questions regarding what dogs you are allowed to adopt Cahill, Mike Director, Animal Health Michael.Cahill@mass.gov 617-626-1794 Cabral, Patricia Shelter and Rescue Coordinator, Animal Health Patricia.Cabral@mass.gov 617-626-1786 Here is a link to the list of approved rescues https://www.mass.gov/service-details/approved-shelter-and-rescue-organizations PROCESS AND REQUIREMENTS APPLICATION: If this dog has stolen your heart and love to offer this extremely bright dog who can make you laugh for hours at his/hers antics don't wait, fill out an application Please apply online now to be considered as a potential adopter. animal.description:
Chip is a little over three months of age.  We are not sure what his breed mix is, but we think he is as cute as a button!  He arrived to us from our Louisiana partner rescue.  He was surrendered to a shelter.  He is a sweet boy that can't wait to find his forever home!  

His foster Mom has this to say about him:

Chip is a real sweetheart!   Super friendly puppy and very athletic.  He has good social skills with other dogs (is tolerant and plays well with our own young pup!), and loves to jump up and cuddle in laps! 

He does have lots of energy so I imagine he would do well in an active family that could take him on long walks or have a fenced in yard for him to run around in, that being said he also seems happy to be mellow in the house. He is working on his housetraining.  

He loves toys!  He is VERY food motivated! 

Adoption fees cover age specific vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm/lyme/ehrlichia test, worming and transport fees. 

Adoption fees: 
Through 6 months of age $450; 
7 months to through 5 years $400; 
6 years and under 9 years $325: bonded pairs are $500; 
9 years and older $250: bonded pairs are $300 

FOR PUPPIES: PLEASE READ!!
Homes considering Puppies must be prepared for:
Flexible Schedules for Potty Training. Puppies can only hold urine for one hour per month of age. Crate Training for the next 10 months to keep them safe from chewing on everything in your home. Supervision with Children and Obedience training. 
Socialization; both with new people, children and other dogs outside of the home.
Homes that want a well behaved dog, must be prepared to put the time, effort and costs associated to train a puppy. Well behaved dogs are not born, they are trained!  Please do not apply for a puppy if you cannot or do not have the time for a puppy.

Almost Home Rescue of New England is a 501 c 3 non-profit rescue; rescuing dogs since 2005. All Adoption applications are completed on line at www.almosthomerescue.net 

This dog is available unless it is marked as Pending, meaning Pending Adoption. This dog is in foster care locally, ONLY if Maine or New Hampshire is listed next to the dogs name; otherwise, the dog is still waiting with our partner rescue for an adoption or foster home in New England. 

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior dogs have a history of being kept up to date on rabies and distemper, have had annual heartworm tests, and are on heartworm preventative at least 6 months of the year. Current pets must by spayed/neutered. 

Imported dogs are transported on a USDA approved transport with a Health Certificate. All imported dogs are quarantined 14 days prior to getting on transport.

animal.description:
This sweet boy is Edward! Edward is a Terrier/ maybe Basset mix who weighs 25 lbs and is about 6 years old. He was saved from a kill shelter by the border of Mexico ands was a special request save from the shelter. He is such a sweetheart and won everyone there over. He does have a deformed front foot that may give him a bit of a hitch in his step but it does not hinder him in any way. He was most likely born with it and as far as he knows, he is perfect! We know dogs like Edward are overlooked for the "perfect" and cuter dogs but we hope there is a family out there that would love to give him a chance and will enjoy the rewards of all the love this boy has to give. He is such a special dog who deserves a chance, a family, and a lifetime of love. We know his amazing family is out there waiting for him!

Edward is located for at our rescue in Texas and is available for adoption and transport to Castle Rock, CO on Feb 13th. He is neutered, up to date on all shots, microchipped and his adoption fee is $375. The fee includes the transport cost. If you would like to add this cutie to your family, please complete an application here-

https://www.tracyspawsrescue.org/adoption-application

Edward is undergoing treatment for Chagas disease. Adopter must commit to the 12 month treatment that costs approximately $25.00 monthly for the medications. Please review this link to better understand Chagas before applying for Edward. https://www.tracyspawsrescue.org/chagas


Services our dogs receive prior to adoption:
Chagas Testing
Heartworm Testing (age appropriate)
Tick Illness Testing (age appropriate)
All age appropriate vaccines
Heartworm and flea/tick preventatives
Spay/neuter surgery
Microchip

CITY, STATE:  Nashville, TN
NAME:  Frieda
AGE:  10 yrs.
SEX:  Female
WEIGHT:  20.86 lbs. (will need your help to lose about 7 lbs.)
COLOR:  Red
COAT:  Long Hair
UP TO DATE:  Yes
SPAYED/NEUTERED:  Yes    DATE:  Before rescue
DHPP:  Yes    DATE:  4/30/2020 (3 yr.)
RABIES:  Yes    DATE:  4/30/2020 (3 yr.)    TAG NUMBER:  321839
ADOPTION FEE:  $200.00 + $20.00 (microchip fee)
HOUSETRAINED:  Yes
CRATE TRAINED:  Yes
LEASH TRAINED:  Yes
FENCED YARD NEEDED:  Yes
SPECIAL NEEDS:  No
HOME W/ SMALL CHILDREN or GRANDCHILDREN:  No
HOME W/ OTHER DOGS:           MALE:  Yes       FEMALE:  Yes
HOME W/ CATS:  Unknown
MICROCHIP BRAND and #:  Avid  082557625   
MONTHLY HEARTWORM DATE:  12th of each month
FOSTER HOME:  Deanna, Decollinss@aol.com
RESCUE #:  2020-12-29-01

BIO UPDATE (1/25/2021):  
If you are home a lot and looking for a companion, Frieda would love to have a home to call her own again.  Once she trusts you, it may take a few days or even a few weeks, she will be your forever companion.  She does very well with other dogs, but prefers the life of a quiet home.  She loves her doggy beds and will sleep there next to your bed all night.  During the day, she will mosey around, take naps, and join you on the couch to lounge some more.  Frieda is not a very active dog, but she does love her meal time!  She is currently on a diet and on a mission to lose another 6 pounds or so.  This girl is so sweet and we are waiting for the perfect home to apply to adopt!  Her wish list includes:
•	A fenced yard
•	Someone home most of the time
•	Someone who has patience because she is terrified
•	Another small dog to keep her company if you have to be gone for any length of time
•	No apartment or high rises

BIO:  Frieda came from middle Tennessee when her owner went into assisted living and had to give her up. 

Frieda was purchased from a breeder at 4 years old and was never socialized before or after purchase. For that reason, she is very timid around new people and has taken sometime to warm up to us.  We see small baby steps each day but whoever adopts her MUST be patient and not push her.  We can tell she wants to be involved with her people, but is just too scared right now. Frieda is doing well on a doggie door but expect accidents until she trusts you enough to have you let her outside. The previous owner said she was not puppy pad trained.

If you are looking to rescue, then here you go... Frieda needs lots of love and patience for her to know she’s safe and that she is with her family for the rest of her life.  

============== Information for All Dogs/Adopters ==============

If you have questions about this dog, please feel free to contact the foster home at the email address listed above.  They have the most up-to-date information concerning the dog and would be happy to answer any questions about the animal. 

We welcome out of state and Canadian adoptions, but we will not ship any dog via cargo.  You will have to make arrangements to pick up the dog or for them to go by ground transport.  If you choose transporting by either volunteers through our organization or by paid transporter, there will be an additional $45 fee added for the required Health Certificate. 

We will not adopt into CT, RI, NH, ME, or MA due to strict laws regarding importation of dogs into those states.  If you have an issue with this, you need to take this up with your legislatures.

To understand the adoption process through AADR, please review the Adoption Information on our home page.  Transportation options are outlined on that page in Step 3.

If you are interested in adopting this Dachshund please review Read Before You Adopt and then you can complete an Application.

THANK YOU FOR YOUR INTEREST IN A RESCUE.

Please don't let the distance stand in your way of finding your newest best friend. We have volunteers that will help your "new friend" get up and down the East Coast. We just can't get them from one Coast to the other but some day we hope to have enough volunteers to do that as well.  For now, please look for dogs on your coast.

Sonrisa, (we call her Sony) is is a 4 lb poodle mix. She was rescued from Rancho Cucamonga. She has some kind of deformity with her mouth specifically her lips. We are still figuring out what exactly is the cause. 

Whether it was congenital or an injury. she is being treated for infection. She can’t close her lips. So it looks like she has a permanent smile. Or snarl. Depending on how you look at it! I like to say it’s a smile. 

She is a sweet girl. She is doing great with other dogs in the foster home. Potty training is good. She needs to gently have her mouth cleaned because it tends to get crusty. It can be tender also. 

She is a 3 year old dog who has a long life to live.

animal.description:
Sweet Cinnamon Tiger was left at a remote rural MS shelter at only six months old (12/28/18) and has lived there until now (1/15/21). Three years! While in the shelter, muscular fifty-five pound 3.5-year-old Cinnamon Tiger lived in a large kennel with two other dogs. He was able to socialize with the staff (they gave him a lot of hugs that he really needed) and go on regular walks. He was deemed healthy, friendly, and eager to please. He does jump on people but that is certainly understandable considering he just wants to love and be loved. With time and training he could learn not to jump. He is being fostered by Krissy who is a pet lover, experienced handler, and owner of a dog grooming salon in Norwood, NJ. He interacts with kids and adults with joy. He is motivated by food, praise, or toys, and is housebroken. He responds well to training. He is confident in new situations, but does look to the handler for guidance. He has shown to be indifferent to cats, but we will not adopt him out to a home that has cats. We are looking for a family who has experience with dogs and is interested in the training process. Cinnamon Tiger is looking for a loving, compassionate family who is patient and diligent in providing decompression time to Tiger as he learns his role in a loving household. To apply to adopt Cinnamon Tiger, please visit our website www.peace4paws.org and fill out an adoption application. Thank you so much!! 


Dog Size Guidelines:
Small: 25 lbs and under (11 kg)
Medium: 26–60 lbs (12 – 27 kg)
Large: 61–100 lbs (28 – 45 kg)
Extra Large: 101 lbs or more (46 kg)

Mason is a 4 month old Shepherd mix. He has a golden yellow, almost red coat. Mason weighs in at 27 pounds. He is quite social with strangers but will benefit from meeting lots of new people to make him a well rounded adult dog. Mason loves to run and play. He is learning quite quickly to sit for a treat. He's definitely food motivated and very smart. Mason is also learning how to walk nicely on a leash and what the world is all about. Mason will need continued obedience training as he does think it's okay to jump up and say hi. We are confident that he will learn that four on the floor is proper dog etiquette. Mason plays very nicely with other dogs and we think he'd adjust to a cat as well. He will require a home that has lots of time to train and socialize him. We think he may be too much for small children, but older ones would be fine.

This 9 year old longhair chihuahua (maybe mixed with papillon?) is a silly fun loving little guy once he bonds with his people, though can be a bit fresh at first meeting new people.  His owner was sadly hospitalized and no longer able to take care of this little guy so he’s looking for a permanent calmer adult home.  He was not housebroken or taken out regularly it seems and is a bit of a marker, so a belly band would be helpful during his adjustment and some patience and consistency as he gets on a schedule.  He can get along with some small female dogs but is the boss and doesn’t like to share attention or food so may be better living as an only dog.  
He has the most adorable underbite and smile and gets so excited to greet his people once he feels comfortable.  Please email njwoof@cs.com and submit an application from www.second chance.petfinder.com to meet him by appointment

animal.description:
Cooper is a handsome boy that arrives to us from our Louisiana partner rescue.  Cooper and his sister Cami are approximately 3 months of age.  Cooper will need to be adopted by a family with previous GSD experience.  This family will need to be able to provide the training and time that a GSD requires to become a good citizen.  


Adoption fees cover age specific vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm/lyme/ehrlichia test, worming and transport fees. 

Adoption fees: 
Through 6 months of age $450; 
7 months to through 5 years $400; 
6 years and under 9 years $325: bonded pairs are $500; 
9 years and older $250: bonded pairs are $300 

FOR PUPPIES: PLEASE READ!!
Homes considering Puppies must be prepared for:
Flexible Schedules for Potty Training. Puppies can only hold urine for one hour per month of age. Crate Training for the next 10 months to keep them safe from chewing on everything in your home. Supervision with Children and Obedience training. 
Socialization; both with new people, children and other dogs outside of the home.
Homes that want a well behaved dog, must be prepared to put the time, effort and costs associated to train a puppy. Well behaved dogs are not born, they are trained!  Please do not apply for a puppy if you cannot or do not have the time for a puppy.

Almost Home Rescue of New England is a 501 c 3 non-profit rescue; rescuing dogs since 2005. All Adoption applications are completed on line at www.almosthomerescue.net 

This dog is available unless it is marked as Pending, meaning Pending Adoption. This dog is in foster care locally, ONLY if Maine or New Hampshire is listed next to the dogs name; otherwise, the dog is still waiting with our partner rescue for an adoption or foster home in New England. 

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior dogs have a history of being kept up to date on rabies and distemper, have had annual heartworm tests, and are on heartworm preventative at least 6 months of the year. Current pets must by spayed/neutered. 

Imported dogs are transported on a USDA approved transport with a Health Certificate. All imported dogs are quarantined 14 days prior to getting on transport.

animal.description:
Sadie is a young...we think probably 2 years old....beagle mix that is mixed
with a bunch of spunk and personality!  She is a super friendly and wants to
greet you with her whole heart and body!  Lots of love pouring out of this
cutie!  Sadie is new to our program but is off to a good start.  She has
been friendly with other animals but might overwhelm a little furry friend
companion but would roll just fine with a dog 30 pounds or larger.  She is
about 25-30 pounds herself.  So far she is doing well with housetraining.
We would love to have a fenced yard for her to sprint around in or a dog
park near.  We will be posting more about her as we learn more but wanted to
quickly get her posted so people could begin to fall in love with her.  She
is currently being fostered in Middle TN in Franklin. If you would like an
adoption application which is how we begin each potential adoption, then
email storkwoods@comcast.net.  

Since she doesn't want to share her bones and
possibly dog food and will need to be fed separately, no small children
would be the best home for her.

animal.description:
This guy is Makas (pronounced Mock-us, Hebrew for hope).  He showed up at a home on 1003.  They put his pictures on FaceBook, but no one claimed.  A kind person took him to the vet (SAH) and had him checked out.  He is guessed to be 7 years old, weighs 40 pounds, was already neutered but not microchipped, received vaccines on Jan 7, but sadly is Heartworm positive. His first treatment for HW is March 9, 2021 (not sure why that far out - was scheduled when the nice lady had him there).

Makas is house trained, but he prefers to be outside.  He does not want to be in a kennel or a fenced area (I've tried both and he escaped from both).   He does come in at night and sleeps on a rug away from the other dogs.  He gets along fine with all the dogs and with the cats.  He does occasionally chase a cat, so I've had to correct him about that.

animal.description:
Meet Beautiful Monroe!

Monroe was picked up by county animal control officers just before Christmas.  Sadly, she was injured and required FHO (Femoral Head Ostectomy) surgery to repair her dislocated hip.  Thank you to our friends at Phoenix Animal Care Coalition (PACC911) who assisted with some of her medical expenses through a critical care grant.

This beautiful female Belgian Malinois is approximately 2-years-old and sweet as sweet can be.  She loves people, loves to play, and most likely will do well with other dogs once properly introduced.

Once she has fully recovered, we know she will have a reputation to maintain as a mali, so an active home which is willing to give her lots of physical and mental stimulation is ideal. 


*****Belgian Malinois Adoption requirements*****

The dog you have selected is a Belgian Malinois.  This is a breed that has very specific needs for an adoptive home.  Because of their need for a high level of exercise, both mentally and physically and their need for ongoing training, only applicants with demonstrated owner/handler experience with this breed will be considered.  The vast majority of them are not best suited as family pets, but in homes with experienced handlers knowledgeable of their needs and breed characteristics.  We will not place in homes with small children or small dogs/cats.  

If you can give Monroe an indoor forever home, please fill out our online application on our website at http://www.savingpawsrescueaz.com/adoption-form/  

 We will only schedule meet and greets with an approved application. We are an all-volunteer organziation.  It may take a couple of days to process an application and complete reference checks.

Thank you for your interest in saving a life!

animal.description:
We are happy to add Missy to our adoptables!!  She has been living at the Our Companions Sanctuary now for almost 6 months and she is now ready for her own home!

She is the cutest black and white pit bull but then we are a bit biased!  When she first came to us from a local animal shelter she was just learning to leash walk, to be polite when greeting people.  She is still a bit of a work in progress on both of those but she is super smart and is catching on fast!  She simply gets so excited to meet new people!

Some of her favorite things are running in one of the play yards-be careful and protect your knees as she is a bit of a bull in a china shop when she gets the zoomies, forgets just how big she is!!  After a good work out she is happy to come back in, rest up in her crate, or cuddle on the couch.  Like any self respecting pit, she is a hard chewer so tough toys are her fave!  She does however take treats very gently so we know she has a soft side too!

She does have some specific requests for her new home-she'd like a single family home (no apartments or condos), be the only animal, active teens or adults, a family that is well versed in pit bull ways, a 6' fence with a yard to run it!  

Stats: 3 yo, 50 lbs, crate trained.  

If you would like to know more about this gorgeous gal please call Our Companions Animal Rescue at 860-242-9999 or e-mail to helpline@ourcompanions.org.

animal.description:
LOOKING FOR AN ANGEL:  8 years old / Approx. 49 lbs. 

Hi, my name is Naomi!  I came to Mostly Mutts from animal control pregnant and with several health issues to address, so Mostly Mutts got right to work helping me to become my healthiest, happiest self.  I am heartworm positive, have glaucoma, some hearing loss and evidence of buckshot pellets under my skin.  My life has been very rough, but I am thankful that only good days and love await me now!

• OTHER DOGS/CATS/KIDS:  I react fearfully to other dogs and lunge at them when they get too close, so I should be your only dog / I did not react at all to the cat in my foster home, so if you have a dog-friendly kitty, let’s meet to see if we can be pals / I’ve met kids at Mostly Mutts and would likely do well with older children (age 15+) who know to go slow with me, as I need time to warm up.  I was nervous and shaking around kids when they ran and were very active.

• PERSONALITY/ENERGY LEVEL:  It seems that I’ve had a pretty tough life thus far, so I am a bit slow and shy to warm up, but I have a sweet nature once I am comfortable.  I am a pretty low-key girl who is quite chill and easy going.  I am not known to bark and I welcome affection from my people once I’m comfortable and trust them.  I get the feeling that my good life is just starting, and I’d love a calm and chill type home in which to relax and thrive / My energy level is a calm 3 – 4 which is good since I need to stay calmer until after my heartworm treatment is completed. (see medical below)

• SKILLS/CRATE/POTTY:  I am a student in the Mostly Mutts University training program, where I am learning lots of great doggie commands with my trainer.  So far, I have mastered ‘sit’, ‘down’ and ‘come’.  I have also shown my good leash manners.  I like treats, so my continued training should be fun / I wasn’t crated in my puppy raising foster home, but my crate manners at Mostly Mutts have been good / My potty manners have been good both at the shelter and in my foster home, so hopefully that will be the case in my new home too.

• LIKES/DISLIKES:  I spent a lot of time outdoors in my life, so I do love soaking up the sun and hanging around sitting outside with my people.  You may also find that I’m drawn to hanging out under a bush or shrubs.  I’d love a fenced yard where I can spend some time outside with you.  Keep an eye on me though, as I did try to dig under the gate in my foster home.  I like having my back scratched and I love a little canned dog food along with my kibble and I enjoy treats too.  I also enjoy going for walks on quiet streets with my people / I sometimes don’t like taking my eyedrops and I can be nervous in new situations or with people I don’t know yet.    

• MEDICAL:  I'm current on vaccinations, micro-chipped and spayed.  I just had my teeth cleaned – likely for the first time in my life!  A grant from the Grey Muzzle Organization paid for me to have that – Thank you!  I am blind in one eye due to glaucoma and have a little loss in the other eye too.  I’ll need drops in both eyes 3 times a day for life and I may go blind in the near future.  I’m also a bit hard of hearing and unfortunately, my previous owner did not keep me on a monthly heartworm preventative, so I am also heartworm positive, but the good news is that Mostly Mutts will cover the cost of my treatment with their vet, so local adoption only, please.  

I am looking for a calm, loving patient family to see me through my heartworm treatment and love me furever!  My adoption fee is $299.00, and I’m located in Kennesaw, Ga.
