animal.description:
Breed: Chihuahua/Miniature Pinscher mix
Sex: Neutered Male
DOB: ~11/20/2017
Weight: 10 lbs
Energy Level: Low-Medium
Personality Type: Gentle, Sweet, Timid
History: Transferred from another shelter
Good With: Dogs, Kids 8+ years
Ideal Home: Any home! Apartments ok!
Fence Requirements: None!
Special Info:

The information we are providing for this animal was developed based on observations and assessments in a shelter or foster environment. We do our best to provide information that will help determine if the dog might be a good fit for you. Please note that behaviors may change in a home environment. We also ask our applicants to assume that any animal they adopt from us will need to be potty trained and learn house manners, although this is not always the case. Our online animal bios are designed to provide as much information as possible and answer some anticipated questions. We do not have the resources to respond to emails with more specific questions.

We are receiving an unusually high number of applications per pet at this time! Please follow the rules below to ensure your application is reviewed; pay attention closely to these instructions because applications will NOT be processed if they are not followed. Please keep in mind that dog/cat availability is currently changing by the hour; you will receive an email if the animal you are interested in is no longer available. New dogs become available almost every day, so feel free to let us know if someone else interests you if your initial choice is already adopted! 

Fill out the application (DOG: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IHD-DOG-Application-9-10-18.pdf, CAT: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/IHD-CAT-Application.pdf) completely. Every question must be answered, and it must be signed. If you are going to type your responses, open the application, save it, type your answers, and save it again. 

-Applicants must be 21+ years old and live within a 50-mile radius of our shelter at 22415 Groesbeck Hwy, Warren 48089.

-You must identify at least 1 dog/cat that you are interested in. If there are multiple dogs/cats, number them in order of priority. 

-Scan a copy of proof of home ownership (i.e. tax bill, deed, or mortgage payment - you can black out the account #, etc.) or animal clause/agreement of your rental agreement.

-Attach the application and home ownership proof/rental agreement animal clause to a new email and send it to bark@iheartdogs.org. The subject line must be formatted to read ""#1 choice of dog/cat, Your First and Last Name"". Example: Subject: Fido, Jane Doe
Once your application is received, it will be assigned to an Adoption Counselor who will follow-up with the applicant who is the best fit within a few days, or to discuss other dogs/cats. It could take up to a couple of weeks for you to receive a final disposition on your application so there is no need to check on the status.

-Introductions will be scheduled by appointment only, 45 minutes per appointment. The entire household, including current dogs, must be present for the appointment. The introductions will take place outside in our parking lot.

-We will continue to perform vet checks for current and prior pets in the household.

-Home visits will be in person for the yard and virtual for inside the home.

-Finalizing the adoption will also be scheduled by appointment.

While this process may seem cumbersome, it is interim during COVID-19, and it is designed to help us respond to the volume of emails we receive every day. Since we are receiving a high volume of applications, please be patient if a dog/cat is no longer available. 

Thank you for your understanding.

 Requirements for Adoption
1. Most of our dogs will require a fenced in yard to allow them to play safely outdoors.

The S.P.C.A. Albrecht Center for Animale Welfare adoption fees vary. Please call the shelter for each pet's adoption fee. 803-648-6863. animal.description:
Murphy is a sweet little peanut. He is a deaf dog,  and he is looking for an ADULT ONLY home. 
He can be a bit anxious at times. He is going to need some very special people who are willing to give him the time and space he needs to feel confident in a new home. Ongoing structure and routine are a must for him. Murphy has lots of silly boxer energy which he needs to burn up.  He loves going for walks and hiking, he's playful and goofy. He is generally happy to greet strangers with that crazy boxer wiggle butt. He has lived with other submissive dogs and a few cats. He's a snuggler when it's on his own terms. He just happens to guard his food but not toys. He's quite an amazing character and deserves someone who will love all of him, including his quirkiness. We are looking for an experienced handler without children. 

If you feel Murphy is a good fit for your home, please submit an adoption application at www.almosthomeri.org

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Dog for a day 1/24:

It was love at first kiss! Karma is pure love - so affectionate and trusting from the moment we pet her. She is a warm and friendly girl with a fantastic temperament. She was easy to walk on the leash and extremely well-behaved. Just saying her name was met by her full attention and eagerness to please no matter what distractions were nearby. She was a great companion who kept up with our pace from a slow stroll to a jog. When she saw other dogs she showed interest but didn't pull hard on the leash or make a sound. She was happy to get affection from everyone who approached her and always received some variant of "What a gorgeous, happy dog you are!" A highlight of our time together was sitting outside at a local brewery where she just layed down under the table, people watched, and seemed like the most content pup in the world. She is super mellow with positive energy and I couldn't stop looking into her gorgeous, soulful eyes. Her name is just perfect for her. Go see and experience her for yourself.

Karma was dumped in a rural area where someone found her. The woman who found her could not keep her as she was moving so she brought her to us at PRBJ. Karma came to us in a rough condition and we are working hard to get her healthy and looking great. She loves attention and affection and knows basic commands such as "sit". She loves people but has challanges with other dogs so she should be the only dog in the home. Karma is a great girl looking for her chance at a forever home. Please fill out an application to meet her and see for yourself how wonderful she can be.

animal.description: Alfie was surrendered to the shelter back in June, when the shelter was closed during quarantine. He is a sweet guy, but is not fond of little kids, which is why he was surrendered, so no kids for this guy. He loves consistency and has made great improvements over the past few months, since he has been able to get consistent exercise. He loves belly rubs and playing fetch in the yard. He is learning how to drop the tennis ball, and he is very treat motivated, and a fast learner. His previous owner stated he lived in a home with another dog, but due to high dog reactivity in the shelter, we are uncertain how he would do with other dogs, so a dog meet is a must. If you think Alfie is a fit for your home, fill out an application and give the shelter a call to schedule a meet.

animal.description:
Peanut is a stunning young boy with the most expressive eyes. He is 12 months old and 18 pounds. He is a sweet boy that gets along with everyone in his foster home - kids, adults, cats and his foster dog sister who he loves to play with. He is an easy going boy that is potty trained and has been given the full run of the house without any issues. He is sweet and loving and likes to be near his people and foster fur sibling. He has some big ears and clearly hears very well and every single time he hears something he will let you know.  Hopefully you will love the sound of his voice as much as he does, lol.  He is recovering from hip surgery and going forward to continue his rehab, he needs a home where he can get exercise throughout the day.  A fenced in yard is a MUST so that he can run multiple times a day. Staying active on his legs is important for his continued recovery.  He has lots of energy, so an active family that can take him out and about and go on walks or hikes would be great!  Having another doggy friend to play with would also be ideal. Peanut is excited to find his forever family, and paws crossed, maybe another fur sibling.  

Are you interested in adopting Peanut or another JCAPL pet you have seen? You'll need to start by completing an adoption application, available online at our website: www.jcapl.org. There is no obligation to adopt by completing an application, however, we do recommend submitting an application as soon as you find an animal you are interested in. We review applications in the order they are received.

Completed applications can be sent via email to adopt@jcapl.org , faxed to 919-300-5524 or delivered in person by visiting us at one of our adoption events on Saturdays at PetSmart in Garner (White Oak Shopping Center). 

We will contact you as soon as possible once we receive your application.

Thanks for thinking adoption!
animal.name: Peanut

Hi, my name is Nathanial, but my close friends call me either Nat or Natty!  Life is so good now and I'm looking for my forever home.  I did have some misfortunes in my previous life and lost one of my legs and my health was very neglected.  Thanks to all of my adoring fans, I'm all fixed up and feeling the best that I ever have!
My personal veterinarian thinks that I'm 10-12 years old.
All I'm really looking for is a nice, soft, cushy bed so I can sit quietly and just be near my humans.
One of my favorite things to do is soak up some sun, whether it's in the house or outside.  
I'm working on getting accustomed to my wheelchair and my foster mom told me that I get to take that to my forever home too.  
My adoption donation is $250.00 because the rescue that I work with, R&R Sanctuary, Inc., has a special program for dogs just like me.  
Orange County, CA

We are happy to help find these great dogs forever homes. Laredo is a fun loving dog who would be great with any family. If you would like to give him a loving home, please complete an application.

Laredo is located in Texas and is available for adoption and transport to Castle Rock, CO on Feb. 13th. He is neutered, up to date on all shots, microchipped and his adoption fee is $375. The fee includes the transport cost. If you would like to add this cutie to your family, please complete an application here-

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.To speed up the adoption process, please complete our Pre-Adoption Application.I am looking for my new forever home.
Prior to adoption I will be altered, vaccinated, health checked, dewormed, and micro-chipped.
Adoption Fee $550 +taxes/feesIf you would like to meet me please fill out a pre-adoption application at www.tailsrescue.orgHappy Tails Adoption Center is open on Sundays from 12-5pm. We are located at 7940 University Ave NE, Fridley. Dogs are at events based on the availability of their foster family. Please fill out a pre-adoption application so we know you are interested in meeting/adopting one of our animals.
The breeds of our dogs and cats are a 'best guess.' We often do not know what mix they are and have to base it on what we think they look like, and base it on breeds often found in the area they came from. Most of our dogs who have gotten DNA tests done are 4-10 breeds mixed together. Because their breed mix is a guess we cannot guarantee a 'full grown size' of many of our younger animals.Interested in adopting me? Click here to fill out an application!Happy Tails Rescue Minnesota is located at 7940 University Ave NE, Fridley MN 55432. We are open for adoption events from 12-5 every Sunday. If there is a certain animal you want to meet at one the events please fill out a preadoption application to directly contact their foster family or check our Facebook page to see if they will be there! Their event attendance is based on the availability of their foster family.
Home visits (video tours or in person) are required for all dog adoptions. All of our cats and dogs are INDOOR pets and are NOT to be left outside unattended (even in a fenced yard), or running loose!

Ginny is sweet, she loves her people.

She takes a little while to develop trust, but she comes around.  She has been through so much.

At the shelter she was the employee favorite, spending time in their office greeting visitors during the day.  Doesn't sound very dangerous to me!

Please come meet Ginny.  She will be a great dog for someone that works or goes to school.  She is content to watch Animal Planet while you are away but will love walks and play time afterward.  She could easily be an apartment dog.

While greyhounds love to run, but they are not highly energetic during the day and Ginny being 5, she is happy just to have a safe and wonderful human that comes home to her.

Please come meet Ginny so she can have the life she should always have had.

602-316-8919 (no texts please)

animal.description:
Milo is very fond of people and their soft sofas! He will gladly chill with you and watch TV or let you do your thing while he naps. He loves walks and is not a puller. Milo was found as a stray and has struggled to find a good fit in a foster. He is too interested in cats and gets bored alone in the yard, but we don't want him to be a yard dog anyway. He gets along with other dogs and loves all humans! He can be trusted in your home alone and does not need to be crated unless only for short periods. He is a young fellow and should have a loving family of his own! He has heartworm disease but the rescue will provide his medication until he tests negative. Because we are foster based, we require an approved application before a meet and greet can be scheduled. We think that is fair for our fosters so every meet and greet has the potential to result in an immediate adoption. The application is available on the rescue website and can be completed online.We work with many rescues and strive to find every rescued dog in our care a great home. Sometimes that means transferring that pet to another location where adoption may be more likely. We currently have partners in New York, Pennsylvania, and Vermont.

If you are interesting in meeting any of our pets, the process is to complete an application. It can be downloaded as a pdf document from our website and submitted by email to WindyRidgeRescue@gmail.com as a scanned document or as photos OR can be completed entirely online. Both links are in the header of our website.

Because we are foster based, we require an approved application to schedule a meet and greet. We feel that is fair to our fosters and rescues so every meet and greet can result in an adoption.

We do not have set adoption fees for dogs, but hope adopters will donate generously so we can rescue more. The medical care for every dog can easily exceed the adoption donation. Average adoption fees for dogs in the area range from $175 up to $450.

We ask for a minimum adoption donation of $50 for cats regardless of age. Each cat is up to date on vaccinations, dewormer, and microchipped. Larger donations are always welcome so we can rescue more. Medical care for each cat easily exceeds the minimum donation.

As with every rescue, our resources are limited and the need for rescue help is unlimited. Your generosity helps us to rescue more.

Adopting or fostering for a rescue frees up a space where a new rescue can reside.

If you can't adopt or foster, than please consider donating.

Jaxson
, he is one little bundle of mystery, love, energy, snuggles, and back to the mystery! We think he is a boxer/black mouth cur BUT no guarantee. We think he will be a medium-size dog BUT he could get a growth spurt.
Jaxson

animal.description:
Maddie was apparently wandering on her own after having a litter of puppies not long ago. A pup friend found her and brought her home to the family house for a bath, a meal, and some tender loving care, and most importantly, a chance for a family of her own. Maddie seems comfortable in the home and likes to be a follower so she doesn't miss any pets or treats. She loves doggie toys and collects them on her bed for safekeeping. She is happy to snuggle with you and nap if you let her! Because we are foster based, we require an approved application before a meet and greet can be scheduled. We think that is fair for our fosters so every meet and greet has the potential to result in an immediate adoption. The application is available on the rescue website and can be completed online.We work with many rescues and strive to find every rescued dog in our care a great home. Sometimes that means transferring that pet to another location where adoption may be more likely. We currently have partners in New York, Pennsylvania, and Vermont.

If you are interesting in meeting any of our pets, the process is to complete an application. It can be downloaded as a pdf document from our website and submitted by email to WindyRidgeRescue@gmail.com as a scanned document or as photos OR can be completed entirely online. Both links are in the header of our website.

Because we are foster based, we require an approved application to schedule a meet and greet. We feel that is fair to our fosters and rescues so every meet and greet can result in an adoption.

We do not have set adoption fees for dogs, but hope adopters will donate generously so we can rescue more. The medical care for every dog can easily exceed the adoption donation. Average adoption fees for dogs in the area range from $175 up to $450.

We ask for a minimum adoption donation of $50 for cats regardless of age. Each cat is up to date on vaccinations, dewormer, and microchipped. Larger donations are always welcome so we can rescue more. Medical care for each cat easily exceeds the minimum donation.

As with every rescue, our resources are limited and the need for rescue help is unlimited. Your generosity helps us to rescue more.

Adopting or fostering for a rescue frees up a space where a new rescue can reside.

If you can't adopt or foster, than please consider donating.

animal.description: What do you get when you combine a little bit of flour and a little bit a fat, and some spice for an extra kick? The perfect Roux of course! At 3 years old, I am a young energetic gent weighing in at 60lbs. You know, there is a Louisiana French phrase that goes Losh pa la pa tot which means dont let go of the potato or dont give up. And that enduring spirit has led me all the way from the South to St.Helens to find my new family! Big and boisterous I still have a lot of puppy like character and a very baby huey playstyle with my dog friends. I am just a big goof and dont have a ton of impulse control just yet, but the ladies say that I am very smart and quick to catch onto the basics like sit. Plus, I am very food motivated which helps with my training. Even though I am just a big oaf, I can still have my sensitive ninny moments, like the other day on my walks some leaves blew all at once and I was like woah what is that and why did it happen? But with some tasty treats, I quickly learned that it wasnt a big deal. Due to my size and careless bounces, I am looking for a house with kiddos over 14 and no kitties. Though dog parks are too much for me, I do enjoy playing one on one with doggies who can keep up with my annoying puppy like antics (and maybe also teach me how to take play breaks!). Handsome, playful, and full of spunk.Roux is going to need an adopter that is able to be around him most of the time. He is very well crate trained and seems to enjoy his time in the crate. He needs frequent potty breaks outside, where he loves to run and play and pick stuff up. He is a very heavy chewer and will need appropriate toys that he won't be able to eat. Roux's adoption fee is $250.00, he is neutered, current on vaccines, treated for fleas and treated for worms. If you are interested in meeting Roux we ask that you please email adoption@columbiahumane.org in order to obtain an application. Please note that all adoptions are done by appointment only. We will only schedule an appointment once you have an approved application on file. Please NO PHONE CALLS, email inquiry's are the easiest way to get ahold of us, as we spend the majority of the days working with our animals and are not available to answer phone calls.For more information call 503-397-4353 or email animalwelfare@columbiahumbia.org

animal.description:
***All animals listed on our website are in private foster homes. To arrange a meet and greet with a dog, you MUST fill out the adoption application so that it can be sent to the foster parent for review to determine if your home is a match for the dog. If a dog receives multiple applications, we operate on a best-fit basis, not first come first served.***


Hi My name is Trudy Judy! I'm a 3 year old hound mix with the sweetest face and biggest most floppiest ears! I'm so sweet and a really good girl. 


I have a very funny personality --- I can be so calm and sleepy for most of the day but when my family starts to move around I definitely want to go see what's happening and play! I also get some fun zoomies after my walks. As I feel better each day I'm more and more ready to play and have fun with my people! 


I'm learning about toys and what's ok and not ok to chew on. I'm pretty smart and have a guilty conscience so I'm learning fast! When I play I fly around in speedy circles -- I'm so gentle but can forget myself a bit when I zoom around and get excited, for that reason I probably would do best in a home without small children so I don't knock them over. 


On walks I do well in my harness. If I pick up a good smell I'll try to follow my nose and may pull a little. Because of my love for sniffing and my playful energy I'd love a home with an active family who will keep me entertained and happy. I'd also ideally love to have another dog and/or a yard for playtime. 


My ideal day would have some snoozies, a few play sessions with my people or dog brother/sister, and time outside to enjoy all the amazing smells! 


I currently live in a foster home with another dog. She's older and doesn't like to play with me and I respect that well. I do sneak in cuddles with her though!! 


I'm crate trained and sleep in my crate at night and when my people are gone. 


I'm a very curious little lady and like to explore all around with my hound nose. 


I am heartworm positive and am receiving treatment from Second Chance. 

I am spayed, up-to-date on vaccinations, microchipped, has been dewormed, and is current on her monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. My adoption fee is $300. If you think I could be the one for you, please fill out an adoption application at www.secondchancenc.org. Thank you!

animal.description:
B is for Ball, and anything else she can play fetch or tug-of-war with. She loves running after anything you throw for her.
E is for Energy. This girl is a riot to watch when you bring out the vacuum cleaner, when she chases her tail, or when she has after-shower zoomies. She loves any toy that squeaks, and her favorite thing of all time is cheese in her WestPaw toy - she will lick and lick and lick to get out every last morsel of cheese.

L is for LOVE. She loves to give it and she loves to receive it. Bella has the best sense of those around her. If I am having a conversation with someone and I become teary she immediately is at my side looking into my eyes and comforting me. She loves to be snuggled and scratched and brushed and played with. 

L is for Lucky. Bella went from being a stray in Texas to having a warm bed to sleep in at night, lots of toys and treats to keep her occupied, and walkies every day!

A is for Awesome! Bella has learned SO much in the time that I've had her. She is a fast learner and wants to make you happy. She has learned, ""sit,"" ""stay,"" ""down,"" ""gimme paw,"" ""high five,"" and we are working on ""leave it."" She LOVES dog food - treat dispenser puzzles and - of course - the aforementioned squeaky toys. 

We have been working on her socialization skills when I can find other confident and calm dogs her size or larger to show her the ropes. She has been very sweet with children, but I live alone so I haven't seen her in a ""living with children"" setting. I have not had the opportunity to see how she responds to cats but she is reactive on a leash when we're out walking and she sees other dogs, so someone who can help her learn leash skills would be a good thing. She does really well in a harness on her walks and pulls much less than with just a collar. She has already made tremendous improvements. 

She would benefit from some basic training and really wants to make her people proud. She would probably be best as an only dog in the home. She has very strong paws and when she plays she can be rambunctious so she needs someone who can help keep her calm, or who can handle her strength. I am working on her not jumping up on her hoomans. She wants to be responsive, but she is learning to stay down while still showing interest. 
She LOVES to go walking, hiking, and wandering, and she was very interested in water when we found a little stream. She walked right into it and loved it. She has webbed feet and the longest dog toes so I'm pretty sure she will be an awesome swimmer. She would LOVE a yard where she can have her morning zoomies and, she would benefit from daily walks. 

She goes in her kennel well, and is very comfortable there, especially with a blanket covering her. But if she knows you're in the other room she might scratch to be with you at night. She is 100% potty trained and does an excellent job! She adjusts to routines very well and hardly makes a peep (unless she hears a knock at the door or the doorbell - we're working on that). 

Her potential forever family needs to be strong and confident in their ability to love her and care for her and remember that she is the rescue, and she is not an emotional support animal. She is sweet and loving, but she will benefit from a routine and extra encouragement and support. 

Dogs are not placed on a first-come, first-serve basis. We strive to find the perfect home for each animal. Applications may take up to 48 hours to process.

All CAWS animals are fixed, microchipped, and vaccinated. Her adoption fee is $200. If you are interested in adopting a CAWS pet, please fill out an online application at http://caws.org/adoption-application If you are interested in adopting a CAWS pet, please fill out an online application at https://caws.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Hey friends! My name is Tilly, and I'm a world class cuddler. I am a 2-year-old Chihuahua who is almost 10lbs and as sweet as can be. I am housetrained and just sleep while my foster mom is gone - I know not to bark or destroy things. I'm a lap dog to my core and really enjoy cuddling and giving kisses. Even though I'm a youngster, I'm a lower energy dog; I do like to run around some, but honestly, I'm more interested in sitting in your lap and watching TV with you. I have met other small dogs and puppies as big as 22# and done totally fine with them, too. If you are looking for a sweet, lowkey, cuddly pup with cute, big ears then reach out to ARNO about coming to meet me! I cannot wait to find my forever home soon!


My adoption fee is $200. This includes a spay/neuter, up-to-date vaccines, deworming, a microchip, a heartworm test, and, if needed, heartworm treatment.

________________________________________________

For more information email: adopt@animalrescueneworleans.org.

To complete an application, please visit: https://animalrescueneworleans.org/adoptfoster/.

________________________________________________

For all animals that have not been spayed or neutered a $100 deposit will be required in addition to the adoption fee. The deposit is refundable upon completion of the spay / neuter surgery.

For more information email: adopt@animalrescueneworleans.org.

To complete an application, please visit: https://animalrescueneworleans.org/adoptfoster/.

I'm housetrained, and my foster mom says my best traits are my playfulness and cuddly personality. I love to play with my toys and with other small dogs - my favorite game to play with them is 'chase'. I have met puppies and did fine with them, too. After some play time, I really enjoy a good cuddle session, and I think that I make an A+ cuddle partner. If you are looking for a playful and snuggly pup with an irresistible smile, I'm the lady for you! I am so excited to find my forever home, and I know I will bring so much joy and laughter to it.

Description of pet
***Before you send us an inquiry, consider if you are actually serious and READY to adopt. We also only adopt within a 2-hour driving distance of Goshen, IN. ***

.***Please know we are not a shelter and are NOT open to the public. All meet and greets are arranged only AFTER an application is submitted and reviewed. 

Sweet Chianti is a knock out in looks and personality, Chianti is a 4-year-old retired racer who recently joined Greyt Angels.  Chianti is adjusting to retirement and enjoying the fenced yard in her foster home and her foster greyhound sibling.  Chianti will be available for adoption shortly and we will update her information as we get to know her.    Chianti will not be available to a home with small children.   For more information on Chianti please email greytangels@gmail.com.

We LOVE the support and interest of every inquiry on our hounds!!! At this time, however, we are a smaller group, so we must limit our adoptions to a two-hour radius of our home base of Goshen, Indiana. This enables us to better provide support to our adopters and our hounds, when needed, for a more successful adoption experience!
